This article is a letter from President Barack Obama to the Speaker of the House, providing a supplemental report on military operations conducted by the United States. The letter addresses operations against al Qa'ida, the Taliban, and associated forces in Afghanistan, as well as the detention operations at Guantanamo Bay. It also mentions military operations in Iraq, Libya, Egypt, maritime interception operations, and U.S./NATO operations in Kosovo. The President asserts that these operations are carried out in accordance with his constitutional and statutory authority as Commander in Chief and Chief Executive.